g.%26quot%3B%20Top%20programmers%20%26quot%3Bwho%20are%20good%20enough%20to%20start%20their%20own%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20can%20still%20command%20top%20salaries%2C%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%20the%20best%20general%20advice%20for%20protecting%20oneself%20from%20AI%20is%20to%20do%20something%20so%20well%20that%20you're%20operating%20way%20above%20the%20level%20of%20scutwork%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Graham%20at%20Y%20Combinator%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraham%20said%20that%20to%20become%20a%20superstar%20in%20your%20chosen%20field%2C%20you've%20got%20to%20have%20passion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20do%20something%20really%20well%20if%20you're%20not%20deeply%20interested%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGraham%20isn't%20the%20only%20one%20who%20has%20acknowledged%20AI's%20disruptive%20potential%20on%20the%20job%20market.%20Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20told%20podcaster%20Joe%20Rogan%20in%20a%20January%20interview%20that%20he%20expects%20AI%20to%20be%20able%20to%20write%20code%20like%20a%20midlevel%20engineer%20within%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%20May%2C%20Anthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%20told%20Axios%20in%20an%20interview%20that%20AI%20could%20wipe%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-warning-ai-could-eliminate-jobs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E50%25%20of%20entry-level%20office%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%20published%20a%20labor%20market%20report%20in%20February%20that%20said%20computer%20science%20graduates%20faced%20an%20unemployment%20rate%20of%206.1%25.%20That%20was%20higher%20than%20other%20majors%2C%20such%20as%20history%20at%204.6%25%20and%20biology%20at%203%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20b